review_blob: Pours hazy with very small head. Nose is slight wet wool and citrus hops. Taste slight malty with notes of mandarins and light maltiness. Quickly fading in the glass but rather well brewed.

Pours hazy with a firm head and a rich hoppy nose. Taste is citric with nice malty notes and some hops
 Palate is rather short but still agreeable.

Probably damaged by yeast or overproteined malt since it was almost impossible to pour. But nose is good, taste is rich in hops and with citric flavours. Palate with a rich and warm bitterness of hops.
On a warm day in Austria this straw coloured light beer was a good match. Firm white head and a light taste with some hops on the palate.

Hazy but dark brown and with a firm beige head. Nose is slightly malty, bready and even a little sweet. Taste is fruityness of malts and spicy notes. Ripe berries and some heat from alcohol is present. Palate medium lasting with some bitterness and also accompanied with alcoholic sweetness.
Pours hazy in amber and with white head. Slight bitterness in the taste bit mostly with slight herbal notes and weak hops. You dont notice that it is dry hopped very much.
Pours hazy with small head and small nose without significance. Taste is herbal with notes of coriander and other green herbs. Palate is short and almost sweet herbal.

Pours in reddish-brown with a firm of white head and a really nice nose of bitter almonds. Even some marcipan and dried fruit. Taste is more fruity with cherry notes and red berries. Palate regains the almonds from the nose and adds some sourness. Some heat as well but still lingering style.

Very light but still fresh on the nose but without significance. Taste is also fresh but leaves untouched. Palate leaving some bitterness of hops but also rather weak. Nice to try it. Agreeable but not repetitive.

Pours in reddish-brown amber with firm of white head. Nose is light sour and malty. Taste is rich malt with herbal grassy notes. Palate also leaves medium long notes of classic malts and some grassy. Enjoyable.
A simple but straight forward Kellerbier in fresh style with light hops. Well brewed but no sensation.

Pours light hazy with a small firm head. Nose is weak but pleasant with slight herbal notes. Taste is slightly bitter with fading hops but leaving a bitter palate. Grassy notes and also taste slight herbal.

Appearance is quite nice but the nose is bakery yeast without finesse. Also taste is yeasty and it takes overhand disguarding the coffee and chocolate taste within. Palate is better but still a little weak.

Beautiful glass with rich head in of white. Nose is malty rich and with some cabbage style. Taste is also almost a little cabbage but rich maltiness and even slight hoppiness. Palate leaves some bitterness and a taste of pineapple with impressive length.
Black with dark red tones and a rich flavour. Taste is woody, rich and with notes of chocolate and coffee. Palate is short on the richness but remaining on bitterness and liquorice taste.
beer_name: Left Hand Fade To Black Vol. 4: Rocky Mountain Black Ale

review_blob: Pours beautifully in reddish-brown almost read. Firm head but small. Balanced sour taste and a rich almst applecidre in the taste with balanced woods and more barrel impressions.

Slight haze in golden colour. Small but firm head and rich malty notes with hint of fudge. Taste is rich malty with ripe fruits and still sweetness and fudge. Palate is rather long and keeping up the maltiness.
Pours amber to gold with rich nose of hops. Taste is slightly malty and with a warm hoppiness. Quite a nice companion.
Pours with a rich white head. Notes of lemongrass and some yeast in nose and taste. Fresh notes of fine hops with a long ending and remaining slight bitterNess and noble fruit.
beer_name: Glazen Toren Saison dErpe-Mere Speciaal Eindejaar

review_blob: Pours hazy but in rich amber colour. Saturated nose with fruits, apricots, peach and some hops. Good texture in taste remaining for the palate. Really nice Belgian companion.

Pours hazy in straw colour with a nice fluffy head. Nose is fruity, apricots and some sweetness. But also hops. Taste is rich in fruit but also typical cascade hints and yeast. Finish is longlasting with clear hops and even some bitterness.

Nose is quite small but giving hints of heavy malt tones. Colour is amber with of white head, quite short but okay. Taste is really malty and herbal with almost spicy notes. Very enjoyable in this style of beer and despite low alcohol it has intense tasting notes and remaining palate.
Pours with a small head but rich note. Malty and with some hops in the palate but still more old fashion in therror style. Nice IPA but not very typical from historic perspective.

Pours hazy with small head but appearance is quite nice. Nose is small with herbal and citric notes and some rich malt. Taste is a really nice pilsner companion with fresh palate and accompanied by citric notes. For my lawnmower the irresistible buddy.

Pouring in straw to gold with some haze and a firm white head. Nose is fresh with almost citric notes and rich aroma. Taste is initially malty but grows with herbs and a little spiciness and of course some yeast. Palate is with slight bitterness and the rich taste is confirmed.
Pouring really dark with small head. Nose and taste is with chocolate and some roasted tones. Palate is a little weak and body thin but still a clean and nice stout.

Pours nice in amber with light but firm head. Nose is interesting with citric tones and some yeast but also leaving some maltiness. Taste is quite OK but palate doesnt really live up to the promises. A little weak at the and. Still ok IPA.
Reddish with firm of white head. Nose with lots of maltiness and almost chestnut in flavour. Also lots of malt in the taste with the same chestnut. Nice companion.
This is fun. Rich nose with dessert, fudge and all of it. Pours in almost dark ruby with small white head. Taste lingering and flattering but not so beerish? Like it as a taste experience.
beer_name: New Belgium + Ben & Jerrys Salted Caramel Brownie Brown Ale

review_blob: Pours in gold with firm head. Typical Belgian yeast and nose in general. Fruity taste with some sourness but a rich maltiness. No dramatic hops at all.

Pours almost with no head at all but in a very clear golden colour. Nose is small malty and with some yeast. Taste is also timid and not very demanding. Palate very short and leaving jobs significant impression. Light and well brewed but no my type of beer.

The Slaapmutske is a neat clear gold appearance in some haze with a white head. Nose is somewhat discrete but okay. Taste is malty with hoppy notes of citrus (pommerance ) and of course yeast. Palate lasting and enjoyable fading in malty notes.

Kehrwieder are always interesting. The Galaxy shows a light brownish colour in hazy mode with a firm head. Yeast and citric on the nose. Comes also in the taste but rounding of with grapefruit and orange zest. Palate fairly longlasting with bitterness from the hops but still keeping the fruit from the malt alive. Nice IPA but not a sensation.
Pours very neatly in amber with clear white firm head. Taste is mild but clear and typical for the Czech type beer. Round palate and not challenging at all.
A nice plain Austrian beer without significant character. Still well brewed and enjoyable in the snow on a mountain.
A nice Czech beer of classic Pilsner type. Nothing really special about it. Nice straw gold colour and white head. Would be better if a little more hops appear on the palate. Nice and clean.
75 cl bottle from Belgoklubben. Pours hazy and whiteish with a short small head. Nice fruity taste with some malty and wheat in the palate. Light and refreshing and typical wit style.

A nice Czech original Pilsener. Pours in golden straw with light head and a malty typical taste for the region. Nicely brewed with a rich malt but weak hop on the palate. On the mountain on a hot summer day Im sure its really good.

Slightly hazy but still a nice pour with a small but nice head. Taste is citric and very refreshing with some malty notes. Palate gives a rich citric onward experience. For such a low ABV beer it is surprisingly rich in taste and palate.

Really black with dark brown head and malty chocolate nose with a touch of coffee. Taste is magnificent and palate leaves a longlasting taste of rich dark notes malt, coffee and choc. Some warn notes left behind...
Nice Czech Pils with some herbal notes. Much is the same in the region but still this one is rather good I must say.
UPDATED: APR 16, 2016
Pours in straw with very small head. Taste is malty with light hops but not significant. Palate leaves you wishing for more hops to fulfil the picture. Nice plain ipa but nothing to write home about.
Well nothing much to say. Plain American beer with no specific character. Really cold on a summer day its enjoyable as thirstquencher.

Well monster is a clear exaggeration. Nice amber colour with tiny head. Nose is malty and with some fading hops. Taste is a little richer but no power. Palate gives some light hops but still not matching the invigorous name. Disappointed but not really bad.
beer_name: Greene King Double Hop Monster (Bottle / Keg)

review_blob: Classic Czech beer in straw yellow with small head. Malty taste with some grassy notes. Palate reveals some hops but still mild ones giving slight bitterness. Nice Pilsner.

From Hamburg bottle pours in straw/amber colour with a white head and a light hoppy but most malty nose. German hops are clearly present and gives a nice change to the extreme citric American hops. A nice brew.
This a very typical north German beer. Nice straw colour and a firm head. Some citric notes on the nose but mostly malt on the tongue. Palate a little weak but pleasant. Nice pils.

A typical us lager with Hawaii notes. I tasted it locally on HI and there it is quite OK on a hot summer day. Back in EU it is a little pale and with light malty notes and no impressive hops. Palate is short but agreeable. A nice local brew if you drink it locally.
Fresh from tap in Bremen. Hazy but still looking good with a fresh nose and firm but fluffy head. Fresh but small in taste and palate leaving shortly. Still a good thirstquencher.
